<section class="accessibility-section" aria-labelledby="accessibility-heading">
    <div class="container">
        <h1 id="accessibility-heading" class="page-title">Accessibility Features</h1>
        
        <p class="intro-text">
            Campus Compass is built with accessibility as a core principle. 
            We believe everyone deserves equal access to information and support.
        </p>
        
        <div class="features-list">
            <article class="feature-item">
                <h2 class="feature-item-title">High Contrast Mode</h2>
                <p class="feature-item-description">
                    Toggle high contrast mode for better visibility. Increases contrast ratios 
                    to meet WCAG AAA standards, making text and UI elements easier to distinguish.
                </p>
                <button class="btn btn-secondary" onclick="document.getElementById('toggle-high-contrast').click()">
                    Try High Contrast Mode
                </button>
            </article>
            
            <article class="feature-item">
                <h2 class="feature-item-title">Dyslexia-Friendly Mode</h2>
                <p class="feature-item-description">
                    Switches to OpenDyslexic font and optimized spacing. Reduces visual stress 
                    and improves readability for users with dyslexia and reading difficulties.
                </p>
                <button class="btn btn-secondary" onclick="document.getElementById('toggle-dyslexia-mode').click()">
                    Try Dyslexia-Friendly Mode
                </button>
            </article>
            
            <article class="feature-item">
                <h2 class="feature-item-title">Text-to-Speech</h2>
                <p class="feature-item-description">
                    Built-in text-to-speech support using the Web Speech API. 
                    Listen to content read aloud, perfect for visually impaired users 
                    or those who prefer auditory learning.
                </p>
                <button class="btn btn-secondary" onclick="document.getElementById('toggle-tts').click()">
                    Try Text-to-Speech
                </button>
            </article>
            
            <article class="feature-item">
                <h2 class="feature-item-title">Keyboard Navigation</h2>
                <p class="feature-item-description">
                    Full keyboard navigation support. All interactive elements are accessible 
                    via keyboard. Tab order is logical, and focus indicators are clearly visible.
                </p>
            </article>
            
            <article class="feature-item">
                <h2 class="feature-item-title">Screen Reader Support</h2>
                <p class="feature-item-description">
                    Semantic HTML, ARIA labels, and proper heading structure ensure 
                    compatibility with screen readers like NVDA, JAWS, and VoiceOver.
                </p>
            </article>
            
            <article class="feature-item">
                <h2 class="feature-item-title">Simple Language & Low Cognitive Load</h2>
                <p class="feature-item-description">
                    Clear, simple language throughout. Minimal distractions, clean layout, 
                    and straightforward navigation reduce cognitive load for all users.
                </p>
            </article>
        </div>
        
        <div class="standards-info">
            <h2 class="standards-title">Accessibility Standards</h2>
            <p class="standards-text">
                Campus Compass aims to meet <strong>WCAG 2.1 Level AA</strong> standards, 
                with many features exceeding to Level AAA. We continuously test with 
                assistive technologies and welcome feedback from users.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
